    {
      "datasource": { "type": "tempo", "uid": "tempo" },
      "title": "How to read these traces",
      "type": "text",
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 17 },
      "id": 4,
      "options": { "mode": "markdown", "content": "Each trace starts at a **frontend** `ui.*` span (the user's click), continues into the **FastAPI** server span via the `traceparent` header, then fans out into `orchestrator.*` phases, **SQLAlchemy** queries (pgvector retrieval), and `llm.generate_text` / `llm.embed_texts` spans carrying model, token counts, and — when `OTEL_CAPTURE_CONTENT=true` — the full prompt and completion.\n\nUse **Explore → Tempo** for ad-hoc TraceQL, or click any log line in **RPG · Logs** to jump straight to its trace via `trace_id`." }
